  <node name="Items" unique_id="16" prog_lang="custom-colors" tags="" readonly="0" custom_icon_id="0" is_bold="0" foreground="" ts_creation="1628005515" ts_lastsave="1628017950">
    <node name="Illaras Amulet" unique_id="18" prog_lang="custom-colors" tags="" readonly="0" custom_icon_id="0" is_bold="0" foreground="" ts_creation="1628017950" ts_lastsave="1633030014">
      <rich_text>Found on </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 6">Illara</rich_text>
      <rich_text> when we found her </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 14">near Blackwater Lake</rich_text>
      <rich_text>.

When she wore the neckless, she looked fine and seemed herself. When she took it of, she became a mindless zombie.

Bonri wore the neckless, he took damage and was unable to remove it.
Trying to attack the amulet to free him caused a burst of energy in the </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 17">stone</rich_text>
      <rich_text>, releasing another ghost to attack us.

We cast identify on the amulet:
- Something is resisting the identification
- It is a cursed magic item
- Standard remove curse spell would remove the item from Bonri
- Item was created by a high level spell
- Like an exchange point for energy, someone using this transfer to release beings into the world
- Bonri's book said we should keep the amulet, don't know where the other end of the transfer is

The </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 25">Duchess</rich_text>
      <rich_text> was able to easily remove the necklace from Bonri, unlike anyone else.</rich_text>
    </node>
    <node name="Magical Stone" unique_id="17" prog_lang="custom-colors" tags="" readonly="0" custom_icon_id="0" is_bold="0" foreground="" ts_creation="1628017713" ts_lastsave="1633034512">
