    <node name="Life in Zoscara" unique_id="24" prog_lang="custom-colors" tags="" readonly="0" custom_icon_id="0" is_bold="0" foreground="" ts_creation="1631817439" ts_lastsave="1633027846">
      <rich_text>Ches 22, Morning

We talked to </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 22">Narissia</rich_text>
      <rich_text> about identifying the </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 18">amulet</rich_text>
      <rich_text>, she told us no magic in the temple or city.
Suggested we might be able to identify items outside city.

The temple could identify, but not before tomorrow (Ches 23).

King's guard and </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 21">Lt. Grey</rich_text>
      <rich_text> arrived to talk to us about the magical items.

She told us that </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 5">Nathaniel</rich_text>
      <rich_text> is being held in </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 13">Zoscara</rich_text>
      <rich_text>, but not due for trial for some time.

She took the box with the </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 17">stone</rich_text>
      <rich_text>, and a bottle of water from </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 14">Blackwater Lake</rich_text>
      <rich_text>. (We didn't tell her about the amulet).


We bought a 100gp pearl at the ‘Pick and Roll’ jewellers to cast identify, using gold loaned to us (for a day) from the temple of Tier.

We sent a letter requesting a meeting with the </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 20">Baron</rich_text>
      <rich_text> (RE Magic items).

Bought some (overly fancy) clothes for Bonri.

We sold our horses to pay back the loan from Narissia.


Chess 22, Sunset

We headed to the tavern called ‘The Well’, following up on the note we received </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 23">earlier</rich_text>
      <rich_text>.

Saw suspicious elf/dwarf/halfling in bar. Dwarf woman headed off down alleyway, followed by Icarus.

Bonri and I headed out the bar and were attacked and abducted by the Duchess.

Woke up at a large, secret party hosted by the Duchess.

She wiped the memory of a guard we mentioned her name to earlier.

She told us Nathaniel could be in trouble, people ‘with his affliction’ don't come out the Baron's Castle.

Gave us a </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 26">task</rich_text>
      <rich_text>, in exchange for which she'd help us with the necklace.
</rich_text>
    </node>
    <node name="Morning Exploration" unique_id="23" prog_lang="custom-colors" tags="" readonly="0" custom_icon_id="0" is_bold="0" foreground="" ts_creation="1630610191" ts_lastsave="1631817619">
      <rich_text>Ches 22, (Early) Morning

Bonri and I decided to explore Zoscara together and investigate the </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 18">necklace</rich_text>
      <rich_text>.

The necklace seemed to drain more life from Bonri overnight.

We went to the archive in Zoscara. They refused to let us in without a permit.

We sold our loot from the </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 14">cave</rich_text>
      <rich_text> from some gold.
The jeweller mentioned Lady Tenika Greytales had had some earings stolen, we could investigate.

Someone gave us a note secretly - “She will meet you, tonight, sunset, the well”</rich_text>
    </node>
    <node name="Terms and Conditions" unique_id="26" prog_lang="custom-colors" tags="" readonly="0" custom_icon_id="0" is_bold="0" foreground="" ts_creation="1633027769" ts_lastsave="1633038347">
      <rich_text>Ches 22, Night

</rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 25">The Duchess</rich_text>
      <rich_text> asked us to kill a man (</rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 28">Therian</rich_text>
      <rich_text>) who wronged her in Zoscara.

She said we'd find him about 2 miles east of Zoscara, in the forest.

She claimed:
	He was planning to give information about her to </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 20">Baron Rickard</rich_text>
      <rich_text>.
	He had a contract with her, and he broke the conditions.
	Therefore he forfits his life.

Icarus didn't want in on the deal, but Bonri, Damiano and I agreed to help.

She took a small amount of our blood, claimed that she could use magic to track us throughout the city.

Gave us teleportation rings with her symbol - we can use these to teleport back to her lair from certain locations.

We set out east to find the man. 

While on route, </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 21">Grey</rich_text>
      <rich_text> gave us a reply to our message - the </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 20">Baron</rich_text>
      <rich_text> agreed to meet us immediately.

We found an abandoned camp at the described location. Maybe Therian was here, but knew we were coming?

Found a </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 29">blackened area and cave</rich_text>
      <rich_text> nearby, similar to near </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 14">Blackwater Lake</rich_text>
      <rich_text>. Using magic, we tracked a group nearby with identical teleportation rings.

A halfling, possibly </rich_text>
      <rich_text link="node 28">Therian</rich_text>
      <rich_text>, was heading through the cave.

Combat:
At the end of the cave was Therian, and a group including a Drow (with a black stone). When the drow saw us, he teleported away.

The drow released some red spiders to attack us. It didn't go well for us.

Therian died.</rich_text>
    </node>
